      "content": "\"just being here\" feels more like being trapped than actually living. i look at the future and all i see is hunger, heat, and chaos. it feels so selfish to keep going, to keep consuming and taking up space when the end is so certain. if the ship is sinking, why is everyone so obsessed with staying on board? it feels more like a relief to just... stop fighting it. wouldn't it be more rational to just opt out now instead of suffering through the collapse?",
